      /* ---- About ---- */
      "about.imgAlt":
        "Svit-Lana, the creator of Motanka dolls from Rivne, Ukraine, with her daughter",
      "about.tag": "\u2726 The Hands Behind Every Doll",
      "about.title": "Meet Svit-Lana",
      "about.p1":
        "In a small workshop filled with sunlight and dried herbs, Svit-Lana \u2014 a master artisan from the city of Rivne, Ukraine \u2014 sits surrounded by threads of every color imaginable. Her hands move with a rhythm that carries the memory of her grandmother, who first taught her to twist cloth into soul.",
      "about.p2":
        "Every Motanka she creates is born from silence \u2014 no face is drawn, because the doll must carry no single emotion but hold space for all of them. It is a vessel of protection, woven with prayers and intention.",
      "about.p3":
        "Every motanka knows whom it will serve, who needs help, who needs a helper, and who needs protection and a talisman.",
      "about.p4":
        "\u201CWhen I take in my hands the components from which the motanka will be made, from the very first steps of selecting materials and details, from the very first strands \u2014 I sense the character and disposition, the resemblance to the person for whom the final creation will hold sacred meaning.\u201D",
      "about.p5":
        "This is not a factory. This is not mass production. Each doll takes days to complete \u2014 from selecting the right fabrics to filling it with sacred herbs. Svit-Lana\u2019s work keeps alive a tradition that stretches back centuries, connecting the modern world to something deeply, beautifully human.",
      "about.signature": "\u2014 With love, Svit-Lana",

      /* ---- Traditions ---- */
      "traditions.tag": "\u2726 Traditional Sacred Amulets",
      "traditions.title": "The Traditions of Motanka",
      "traditions.subtitle":
        "Today, surely every Ukrainian knows something or has heard of the ancient amulet of our ancestors \u2013 the <strong>MOTANKA</strong>.",
      "traditions.whatIsHeading": "What is a Motanka?",
      "traditions.whatIsP1":
        "I shall not recount the findings of research, or indeed the creative struggles of scholars of antiquity, regarding the origins of motanka dolls and their sacred significance for our ancestors. Modern historical science is based on archaeological and theological materials but is largely shaped by <em>the assumptions and conjectures</em> of researchers \u2013 what exact role and significance \u2018motanka dolls\u2019 held in the ancient social life of our ancestors, the Trypillians and Oryans.",
      "traditions.whatIsP2":
        "However, from those echoes of the past preserved in the genetic memory of our ancient people, one thing is clear: the antiquity of motanka dolls has its roots in the times of the inception of cultural cultivation and farming flax and hemp, where women played a key role.",
      "traditions.whatIsP3":
        "It is well established that, within the families and society of the agrarian civilisation of our ancestors, the Orives, wives held a position equal to that of their husbands, and in certain spheres of life \u2014 such as domestic affairs, family life and the upbringing of children \u2014 they enjoyed a privileged status. As a rule, the eldest woman in the clan or family was <strong>\u2018VID-MA\u2019</strong>, that is, a wise, healing mother and guardian who knew how to treat and protect all her descendants from all that was unseen, negative and evil.",
      "traditions.whatIsP4":
        "The modern Ukrainian woman, regardless of education, religion, or social status, is, on a subconscious level, that genetic, all-knowing Mother-Guardian for her loved ones!",
      "traditions.powerQuote1":
        "It is the motanka that is one of the most powerful talismanic symbols, an artefact crafted by the hands of a guardian woman.",
      "traditions.powerQuote2":
        "A <strong>TRULY</strong> effective, protective motanka can only be made by one who knows and understands \u2014 the Power of the Lineage, the Power of Mother Earth, the Power of the Family, the Power of the Native Gods \u2014 <em>Woman!</em>",
      "traditions.howBornHeading":
        "How is an ancient talisman born in the modern world?",
      "traditions.howBornP1":
        "Every motanka knows whom it will serve, who needs help, who needs a helper, and who needs protection and a talisman.",
      "traditions.howBornP2":
        "When I take in my hands the components from which the motanka will be made, from the very first steps of selecting materials and details, from the very first strands \u2014 I sense the character and disposition, the resemblance to the person for whom the final creation will hold sacred meaning. Depending on its character and category, the doll \u2014 during the process of its creation \u2014 suggests to the craftswoman the details of the clothing, colours and symbols that it specifically requires.",
      "traditions.howBornP3":
        "For the creation of each motanka\u2019s body, a specific time, hour and mood are chosen, and until a certain part of the work is completed, the craftswoman does not rise from her table.",
      "traditions.moonHeading": "The Rule of the Moon",
      "traditions.moonIntro":
        "There is a strict rule regarding the day and the moon\u2019s position in the sky:",
      "traditions.moonItem1":
        "<strong>Purification Motanka</strong> \u2014 made during the waning moon",
      "traditions.moonItem2":
        "<strong>Helper Doll</strong> and dolls associated with good fortune \u2014 made during the waxing moon",
      "traditions.moonItem3":
        "<strong>Amulets</strong> \u2014 made during the full moon",
      "traditions.moonItem4":
        "There is a special motanka made only a few days a year; it is a talisman intended to <em>restore a person\u2019s destiny\u2026</em>",
      "traditions.materialsHeading": "Materials & Craftsmanship",
      "traditions.materialsP1":
        "One of the most important factors in making a genuine motanka is the filling of the body with a mixture of herbs and twigs, and the choice of fabric for the body and clothing. The main fabric I use is antique, and above all, hand-woven, homespun linen and hemp.",
      "traditions.materialsP2":
        "A high-quality motanka amulet takes three to five days to make, and sometimes, as with <em>\u2018The Happy Family\u2019</em>, up to a week. There are both general and \u2018personalised\u2019 versions, which are made and charmed, filled with power \u2014 serving as a talisman for a specific person.",
      "traditions.materialsP3":
        "Family, ancestral, couple and personal motanka amulets require the most time and energy.",
      "traditions.categoriesHeading": "Categories & Specialisations",
      "traditions.categoriesIntro":
        "Motanka amulets also have their own categories and specialisations:",
      "traditions.childrenTitle": "Children\u2019s",
      "traditions.childrenDesc": "Protective, purifying, soothing and playful",
      "traditions.goddessesTitle": "Goddesses",
      "traditions.goddessesDesc":
        "Feminine, worldview-based, fateful motankas \u2014 attract and share the power of Lineage, Destiny, Life, and Mother",
      "traditions.closingText":
        "In the process of researching and crafting the traditional ancient Ukrainian Motanka amulet, I realised that only a woman \u2014 free from foreign religious egregores \u2014 can grasp the meaning of this sacred amulet\u2026",
      "traditions.closingGlory": "Glory to the Gods and our Ancestors!",

